value:
These clothes are from a past that
was lost to me. They are all that
remain of that hope I once had.

Corrin, queen of some other world,
is said to have chosen her path...yet
mine is a closed loop.

There is something I must say to you,
but now is not the time. It must wait
until we reach the end of this cycle...

What am I doing here, now, dressed
like this? This should be impossible...
Has the cycle...been broken?

In my hands I hold hope and despair.
I have made them both my weapons.

So this is the version of you
who shares a timeline with
$Nf, hm?

The future cannot be changed.
Everything faces annihilation in
the end...
Unending despair.
Completely meaningless...

Even in an endless cycle, I somehow
am made to grow stronger still...

Seiðr? No...that name is a thing of
the past. I am Gullveig, the Golden
Seer, whose life is a cycle unending.

I was not born...$k$pIt is not that I have no memory.
It is that my birth has never occurred.$k$p...Nor do I die.$k$pThe cycle is set. There is no future
in which I will perish.$k$pAnd yet...something is different
here in this world, this time,
this...existence.$k$pI seem to be freed of the cycle's
influence and demands.$k$pWhich means I may see a new future,
events I've never witnessed in all the
cycles of my being... We shall see.
Fade away!
Your future is set.
Once more, once more!
The cycle's power!
All is meaningless...
This clothing reminds me of long ago—though the fit is not as I remember.
You mistook me for Seiðr? Be honest. That isn't true.
Wearing this, my heart has been spirited right to those days...
I have lived the cycle of grief so many times, I am nearly worn through...
I remember when I knew only light and hope...when I was Seiðr...
I am the Golden Seer. My purpose is to bring ruin.
If only we— *sigh* No. It is nothing.
It will be so.
It matters not.
As always...
